                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410510-name-1311" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1311" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1311" type="surname" value="HAMLING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-1311" type="given" value="JONAS"></interp>JONAS HAMLING</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a scaleboard-cutter, in Union-street, Lambeth-walk. The prisoners were my journeymen—on the morning of the 24th of April I was in my bed-room, and saw Roberts crossing my yard, coming from a shed, with the scaleboards on his shoulder—I ran down, and found him in the act of closing my yard-gate, and coming back without them—I ran out, and found-Matthews with the boards on his shoulder—I told him to come back, which he did, and threw them down—I gave them into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Roberts's Defence.</hi> I went to work in the workshop; I saw the yard-gate open; as I came back from shutting the gate, my master ran part me; I had not the boards on my shoulder; he brought Matthews back.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HAMLING</hi> 
